There is a reason the line is so long. Make sure to get there at least a 1/4 to 11am if you want to be one of the first few through the door, or have a large party. The pasta dishes are cooked perfectly. The pasta is cooked perfectly There are a few regular items like the bologenese, but the other two pastas usually rotate each day. There are usually only three to four pastas  dishes to select done. You can't go wrong with any choice you make. My favorite was probably a squash puree sauce. The focaccia is soft and buttery. The last time we went they had shortbread cookies displayed strategically at the cash register so I picked up one each for people in my party. Good thing I did I don't think any of us would have shared.